 oesophageal epithelium is maintained by a single cycling progenitor cell
 population in which cell division can lead to all three possible fate outcomes;
 two daughters that go on to divide, two cells that exit cycle and then
 stratify out of the basal layer, or one daughter that goes on to divide
 and one that differentiates 
