 In particular, since clones induced at 48 hpf involve very few three-cell
 clones, PD divisions must be suppressed at these later times.
 Thus, there must be at least two such changes, to start and then stop PD
 divisions; we assume that there are only these two.
 Indeed, the proportion of four-cell to two-cell clones suggests that one
 in five cell divisions involves symmetrical self-renewal, while the remaining
